{"id":3714,"date":"2013-04-03T16:30:11","date_gmt":"2013-04-03T22:30:11","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/?p=3714"},"modified":"2018-12-07T13:18:30","modified_gmt":"2018-12-07T20:18:30","slug":"what-to-look-for-when-buying-succulents","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/what-to-look-for-when-buying-succulents\/","title":{"rendered":"A guide for buying succulents that are right for you!"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not sure where to start when buying a succulent? I\u2019ve done the hard work for you. Follow my advice and you\u2019ll be confidently buying succulents in no time!<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<p>Buying succulents is so much fun! They're all so beautiful and unique so it can be hard to pick just the right one.<\/p>\n<p>Then again, you might know exactly what you want already. Before you take your shopping trip, whether locally or online, this post will help you determine the perfect succulents for you.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-11499\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy.jpg\" alt=\"This post totally explained why I've been buying succulents all wrong! Now I know what I should buy!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/This-post-totally-explained-why-Ive-been-buying-succulents-all-wrong-Now-I-know-what-I-should-buy.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>What\u2019s your succulent style?<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You might be the kind to give your plants too much attention, or you might totally neglect them. Maybe you\u2019re like me and are non-committal: sometimes giving lots of love and other times utterly neglecting your plants. \u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>Depending on how you care for succulents, and where you live, you'll want to select different plants. For example, Haworthia fasciata is a great option for indoor growers. But, Echeveria varieties prefer to be outside with lots of sunlight.<\/p>\n<p>If you tend to water your plants a lot, Portulacaria afra is a great option. If you rarely remember to water, try a cactus or succulent with very thick leaves.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-3 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-2 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><h4>What size should you get?<\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Succulents come in a wide variety of sizes and with that variation you\u2019ll also get a variety of prices and you\u2019ll find some sizes are easier to care for. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Larger plants are less fickle. They don\u2019t dry out as quickly, so they don\u2019t need as frequent watering. The larger the pot, the easier (generally) it will be to maintain your plant. A succulent in a gallon sized pot will be lower maintenance than a 6 inch pot, which will be lower maintenance than a 4 inch pot, and so on. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A succulent in a larger pot will cost more, but if it means you\u2019re less likely to kill it\u2026 seems worth it to me! <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Two alternatives to potted succulents are <a href=\"https:\/\/thesucculentsource.com\/collections\/succulent-cuttings?aff=20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">cuttings<\/a> (succulents without roots) and <a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/wholesale-plugs\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">plugs<\/a> (like cuttings but with roots and a little soil). <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/thesucculentsource.com\/collections\/succulent-cuttings?aff=20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">Cuttings<\/a> are easier to work with since you don\u2019t have to worry about roots, and they\u2019re much cheaper! They\u2019re generally a little more needy than a fully rooted plant, but not too bad overall.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-11501\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent cuttings are a great way to get lots of succulents at a low price\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-585x877.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Succulent-cuttings-are-a-great-way-to-get-lots-of-succulents-at-a-low-price.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/wholesale-plugs\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">Plugs<\/a> are somewhere in between cuttings and a 2\u201d potted succulent. They start growing more quickly than cuttings, but can still be a bit temperamental.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-11502\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents.jpg\" alt=\"Plugs are a good way to get a wholesale pricing on succulents\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Plugs-are-a-good-way-to-get-a-wholesale-pricing-on-succulents.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now that you\u2019ve found the right plant for you and know what size to get, you may be thinking, <\/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u201cThat\u2019s great! I know what to get, but where do I actually buy them?\u201d<\/span><\/i><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can buy locally at various stores or nurseries, as well as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/where-to-buy-succulents\/\">online<\/a>. There\u2019s benefits to both.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3>Buying Local<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can buy them at a variety of stores depending on where you live. A few places I\u2019ve been able to find succulents locally are:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Home Depot<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lowes<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Walmart<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Local nurseries<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Farmer\u2019s Markets<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I prefer local nurseries or even farmers markets if you have them. They tend to be higher quality and less likely to be over watered. \u00a0Since succulents are really popular, I\u2019ve found more local nurseries are carrying them. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you aren\u2019t sure if a local nursery carries succulents, give them a call. \u00a0You can search for your city or area and \u201csucculents\u201d on Google to find the nurseries closest to you.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-11503\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent.jpg\" alt=\"Buying succulents locally is a great way to pick out the perfect succulent\" width=\"735\" height=\"490\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-80x53.jpg 80w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-200x133.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-250x167.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-585x390.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Buying-succulents-locally-is-a-great-way-to-pick-out-the-perfect-succulent.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some advantages to buying locally are being able to choose the specific plant, as well as quality and quantity. \u00a0Of course, there are also some downsides. Not all areas have stores that sell succulents. There are typically fewer unusual varieties. Local shops don\u2019t specialize in succulents, so plants can be less healthy.<\/span><\/p>\n<h4>Choose the Healthiest Plant<\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This one may seem obvious but&#8230; when you buy at a local store avoid damaged plants \u2013 this means no bumps, no scars, no bugs, and no mushy spots. You can slightly bump the leaves to make sure they don\u2019t fall off. Be sure to do this very gently, but this is one of the early signs to tell if a succulent has been overwatered. The leaves should feel firm, not mushy or squishy.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another thing to look for is color. Brighter colors equal a healthier, better maintained plant. Usually this is just a matter of them getting enough light.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"size-full wp-image-11402\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot.jpg\" alt=\"Echeveria succulents appreciate warm climates, but not too hot\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/10\/Echeveria-succulents-appreciate-warm-climates-but-not-too-hot.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch for multiple plants in the pot. \u00a0It\u2019s like getting plants for free! \u00a0Sometimes I\u2019ll pick out a plant that doesn\u2019t look quite as good because it has multiple plants in it. I know I can help it look better and get more plants out of it.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-11504\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money.jpg\" alt=\"When shopping for succulents, look for a pot that has several in it to get more for your money\" width=\"735\" height=\"1103\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-53x80.jpg 53w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-250x375.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-585x878.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/When-shopping-for-succulents-look-for-a-pot-that-has-several-in-it-to-get-more-for-your-money.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not all succulents will come with more than one succulent in the pot; it really depends on the variety. If you only see one plant in the pot, lift up the leaves a little and see if there\u2019s any new growth hiding. \u00a0I\u2019m always surprised how many have babies growing!<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, don\u2019t buy anything that has been painted! It\u2019s crazy to me that these exist, but if you do see succulents that are glittering or are royal blue, it\u2019s likely they\u2019ve been spray painted. Buying these is just not a good idea. They may look fun, but in the long run, you will have more success with a healthier plant that has not been painted.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3>Buying Online<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As you likely guessed, the pros and cons to buying online are essentially the opposite of buying locally.<\/span><\/p>\n<h4>Benefits to buying online<\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One great thing about buying online is the access to a wider variety of succulents. \u00a0There are also better specimens, because sellers are experts. \u00a0You also get the plants delivered to your door \u2013 you don\u2019t have to go out to go shopping!<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The downsides to online ordering are that you can\u2019t pick your specimen, plants can be damaged in shipping, and are also more expensive.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now, this isn\u2019t really a downside, but almost always plants purchased online may be a little dirty when they arrive. \u00a0Simply use a soft brush to remove the soil. \u00a0I also use an air compressor, so if you have one that\u2019s a great option! Do not use canned air though! It will damage the succulent\u2019s leaves.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-11505\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online.jpg\" alt=\"You'll find an incredible selection of succulents available for sale online\" width=\"735\" height=\"490\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-80x53.jpg 80w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-200x133.jpg 200w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-250x167.jpg 250w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-400x267.jpg 400w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-585x390.jpg 585w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/04\/Youll-find-an-incredible-selection-of-succulents-available-for-sale-online.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<h4>Where to buy online<\/h4>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Good news for you\u2026 I\u2019m an expert at buying succulents online! I\u2019ve ordered from dozens of online shops so I know a thing or two. Here are my favorite places to purchase succulents online:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/mountaincrestgardens.com\/?aff=2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">Mountain Crest Gardens<\/a> (my personal, go-to source)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.leafandclay.co?rfsn=376597.71f09\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Leaf and Clay<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/thesucculentsource.com\/?aff=20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Succulent Source<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/lookingsharpcactus.com\/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looking Sharp Cactus<\/span><\/a><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-