om the following online stores, I\u2019ve heard great things and they ship to a lot of different countries!<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Surreal Succulents (<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/surrealsucculents.co.uk\/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https:\/\/surrealsucculents.co.uk\/<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Succulents Canada (<\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/www.succulents.ca\/buy-plants-online.html\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">http:\/\/www.succulents.ca\/buy-plants-online.html<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> &#8212; Canada only)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Plants Guru (<\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/www.plantsguru.com\/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">http:\/\/www.plantsguru.com\/<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> &#8212; India and UK)<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also check with different Etsy shops. You\u2019ll find some who are located outside the US or willing to ship to many different countries.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3>Replanting<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you\u2019ve purchased your succulents, it\u2019s a good idea to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/how-to-plant-a-succulent\/\">replant them<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u00a0as soon as possible. \u00a0A lot of times the soil succulents are planted in is not ideal for long-term growth. Plus, they are often root-bound, meaning the roots aren\u2019t able to spread out, so they need more space to grow. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I use <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/category\/premixed-bonsai-soil\/succulent-soil\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow sponsored\">Bonsai Jack<\/a> for my indoor succulent soil, and have never been disappointed. It drains well and has the perfect particle size. Soil is really important for healthy succulents. You can <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/well-draining-soil-for-succulent-container-gardens\/\">learn more about it here<\/a>.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-6543\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/10\/Keep-your-succulents-growing-their-best-by-using-well-draining-soil.jpg\" alt=\"Keep your succulents growing their best by using well draining soil\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/10\/Keep-your-succulents-growing-their-best-by-using-well-draining-soil-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/10\/Keep-your-succulents-growing-their-best-by-using-well-draining-soil-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/10\/Keep-your-succulents-growing-their-best-by-using-well-draining-soil.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now that you know the pros and cons to buying succulents locally or online, it\u2019s your turn! Decide which option is best for you, and follow my tips for getting the best succulent you can.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":7,"featured_media":11507,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[66,1],"tags":[81],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3714"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/7"}],"replies